1
00:00:14,970 --> 00:00:15,940
Class of 2021

2
00:00:44,630 --> 00:00:45,450
Noo Rann.

3
00:00:51,440 --> 00:00:54,570
P’ Le, you’re doing it again.

4
00:00:57,900 --> 00:00:58,780
Tired?

5
00:01:01,380 --> 00:01:05,250
Yeah. Why does graduation
have to be this exhausting?

6
00:01:07,320 --> 00:01:08,110
Then let’s go.

7
00:01:09,580 --> 00:01:10,430
Go where?

8
00:01:10,470 --> 00:01:12,920
Well, go home, of course, Miss Graduate.

9
00:01:13,190 --> 00:01:14,870
Are you planning to sit here forever?

10
00:01:15,480 --> 00:01:19,610
Come on, let’s go home.
This pretty big sis will give you a ride.

11
00:01:38,710 --> 00:01:41,259
You finally got First-Class Honors, just as expected.

12
00:01:41,570 --> 00:01:44,590
I knew you’d get it.
It’s not surprising at all.

13
00:01:44,990 --> 00:01:46,970
You’re a front-row kid, after all.

14
00:01:47,960 --> 00:01:49,500
Don’t tease me, P’ Le.

15
00:01:50,009 --> 00:01:51,950
You make it sound like all I ever do is study.

16
00:01:52,170 --> 00:01:53,180
Isn’t it true?

17
00:01:55,789 --> 00:01:58,370
Congrats on finishing your studies.

18
00:02:00,910 --> 00:02:02,740
Thank you.

19
00:02:35,450 --> 00:02:36,829
What did you think I was gonna do?

20
00:02:37,720 --> 00:02:38,710
Well?

21
00:02:40,150 --> 00:02:41,400
You’re teasing me again.

22
00:02:43,960 --> 00:02:44,960
Something on my face?

23
00:02:47,220 --> 00:02:49,030
There, there, there.

24
00:03:00,340 --> 00:03:01,140
P' Le.

25
00:03:02,970 --> 00:03:05,440
I got a full scholarship to study in England.

26
00:03:11,090 --> 00:03:14,330
See? I told you you’d get it.

27
00:03:14,880 --> 00:03:16,910
And you still insist
you’re not all about studying.

28
00:03:17,590 --> 00:03:20,100
Looks like we need to celebrate.

29
00:03:21,370 --> 00:03:24,310
I’ll treat you to anything you want today.

30
00:03:25,160 --> 00:03:27,300
And don’t even try to stop me.

31
00:03:27,650 --> 00:03:31,850
I’ve got a job now.
I’m smart and rich too, you know.

32
00:03:38,720 --> 00:03:41,300
Yes, you’re talented.

33
00:03:42,380 --> 00:03:43,320
Very talented.

34
00:03:44,079 --> 00:03:48,320
You’re beautiful, cool, and mature.

35
00:03:49,010 --> 00:03:52,130
And… you’re someone important to me.

36
00:03:53,220 --> 00:03:54,110
P’ Le.

37
00:03:56,500 --> 00:03:57,820
Yes, Noo Rann?

38
00:04:48,790 --> 00:04:50,710
- P’ Le…
- Get out of my sight.

39
00:05:48,070 --> 00:05:52,810
Five Years Later
London, 2026

40
00:06:57,080 --> 00:07:00,790
If I hadn’t done what I did that day...

41
00:07:12,300 --> 00:07:13,520
What the hell am I doing?

42
00:07:15,180 --> 00:07:17,000
She’s probably forgotten all about me by now.

43
00:08:51,470 --> 00:08:54,850
I hope you're always happy.

44
00:08:56,410 --> 00:08:57,220
P’ Le.

45
00:08:59,660 --> 00:09:03,310
I want you to be happy, Rann.
Happier than anyone else.

46
00:09:03,820 --> 00:09:05,590
The happiest in the whole world.

47
00:09:22,350 --> 00:09:23,360
What is this?

48
00:09:24,420 --> 00:09:25,600
Is this some kind of joke?

49
00:09:26,410 --> 00:09:28,350
You think I wouldn’t recognize your handwriting?

50
00:09:29,130 --> 00:09:31,840
No matter how many years
go by, I could never forget it.

51
00:09:32,870 --> 00:09:36,180
And it’s been five years—five whole
years without a single message.

52
00:09:36,600 --> 00:09:38,670
No updates, no calls back.

53
00:09:40,300 --> 00:09:42,140
If you were going to push me away in disgust…

54
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:45,670
why toy with my heart again?

55
00:10:40,300 --> 00:10:41,980
This time, we need to talk things through.

56
00:11:05,290 --> 00:11:06,610
You, go check.

57
00:11:29,070 --> 00:11:30,630
Hey! What’s the situation?!

58
00:11:35,810 --> 00:11:36,590
Run!

59
00:11:56,520 --> 00:11:57,960
How did they find out we were here?

60
00:11:58,150 --> 00:12:00,670
How would I know?
I’m right here with you.

61
00:12:01,390 --> 00:12:02,920
Looks like we won’t make it out alive.

62
00:12:10,160 --> 00:12:14,530
Well, at least you got to do
what you wanted before dying, boss.

63
00:12:15,380 --> 00:12:17,610
Be grateful your package even made it safely.

64
00:12:18,500 --> 00:12:21,310
Look at me, I don’t even have a wife yet.

65
00:12:22,170 --> 00:12:23,250
Funny much?

66
00:12:26,350 --> 00:12:27,560
Then give me one last laugh.

67
00:12:28,770 --> 00:12:34,100
Come on, at least I want to be
a funny ghost, not some vengeful spirit.

68
00:12:36,630 --> 00:12:38,880
Fuck! Will you just stop shooting?!

69
00:12:41,380 --> 00:12:42,430
Don’t die on me, boss.

70
00:12:43,070 --> 00:12:44,000
You too.

71
00:12:48,560 --> 00:12:49,310
Go.

72
00:13:18,540 --> 00:13:19,350
I knew it.

73
00:15:32,920 --> 00:15:34,600
My condolences, sir.

74
00:16:32,850 --> 00:16:33,700
This isn’t real.

75
00:16:39,610 --> 00:16:40,470
Why?

76
00:16:52,680 --> 00:16:55,830
And this is how we meet again after five years.

77
00:17:12,619 --> 00:17:13,640
Hey.

78
00:17:14,599 --> 00:17:17,609
It’s so sad, isn’t it?
She was still so young.

79
00:17:18,670 --> 00:17:22,200
The one who has it the hardest
is Khun Kanin over there.

80
00:17:22,800 --> 00:17:25,700
His only child passed away so suddenly.

81
00:17:26,050 --> 00:17:29,120
I heard that in just a few months,
he was planning to step back

82
00:17:29,150 --> 00:17:31,240
and let Lené take over the company.

83
00:17:31,560 --> 00:17:35,920
Who knows what’s going to happen
to Khun Kanin and the company now?

84
00:17:36,680 --> 00:17:37,690
Exactly.

85
00:17:38,280 --> 00:17:39,280
What happened to her?

86
00:17:39,940 --> 00:17:43,190
I don’t dare go talk to Khun Kanin.
Don’t want to reopen the wound.

87
00:17:44,070 --> 00:17:46,120
Heard it was a car-related accident.

88
00:17:47,830 --> 00:17:48,950
You guys didn’t know?

89
00:17:49,320 --> 00:17:51,800
I heard there were a lot
of strange things that night.

90
00:17:52,110 --> 00:17:56,560
There isn’t much info, but there are
rumors going around that Khun Lené got…

91
00:18:09,110 --> 00:18:09,900
Khun Rann?

92
00:18:24,930 --> 00:18:28,620
At least… the package made it to you.

93
00:18:34,940 --> 00:18:38,400
My boss was very worried you might not accept it.

94
00:18:42,670 --> 00:18:45,490
She would’ve been happy that you came.

95
00:18:57,410 --> 00:18:58,520
I’m sorry for your loss.

96
00:20:11,360 --> 00:20:12,170
Grandma.

97
00:20:16,260 --> 00:20:18,670
I made it to the freshman welcoming ceremony today.

98
00:20:20,700 --> 00:20:22,380
I wish you were here to see it.

99
00:20:50,260 --> 00:20:52,630
Grandma, I'm sorry.

100
00:20:54,520 --> 00:20:57,080
But I really can’t take it anymore.

101
00:20:58,040 --> 00:21:00,070
I just can’t, Grandma.

102
00:21:16,220 --> 00:21:17,490
I didn’t see anything at all.

103
00:21:19,850 --> 00:21:21,350
I just want to get some fresh air.

104
00:21:22,260 --> 00:21:23,310
It’s hot in there.

105
00:21:24,870 --> 00:21:28,590
Everyone else can do whatever they want.

106
00:21:47,480 --> 00:21:51,520
I once had a cold but still had
to lead the chanting in school.

107
00:21:53,340 --> 00:21:56,530
I sneezed into the microphone
so hard that it short-circuited.

108
00:22:07,720 --> 00:22:09,090
We don’t know each other.

109
00:22:11,700 --> 00:22:13,890
Just think of it as talking to a stranger.

110
00:22:14,120 --> 00:22:16,150
Someone you might not even remember tomorrow.

111
00:22:28,110 --> 00:22:31,390
Senior, if I say something…

112
00:22:34,110 --> 00:22:35,370
please don’t scold me.

113
00:22:43,970 --> 00:22:46,570
My parents passed away when I was young.

114
00:22:49,370 --> 00:22:51,640
Grandma was the one who took care of me.

115
00:22:54,240 --> 00:22:56,810
She was the only family I ever had.

116
00:23:03,480 --> 00:23:04,970
But she’s gone now.

117
00:23:10,090 --> 00:23:14,570
When I got accepted, I wanted
her to be the first one to see it.

118
00:23:15,830 --> 00:23:20,780
I wanted to make her proud, to show
her that her granddaughter could do it.

119
00:23:22,280 --> 00:23:23,120
But…

120
00:23:25,180 --> 00:23:28,630
But then the hospital called and
told me that her heart had failed…

121
00:23:31,930 --> 00:23:34,310
Grandma said the student uniform was beautiful.

122
00:23:35,310 --> 00:23:36,820
She wanted to see me wear it.

123
00:23:39,070 --> 00:23:42,210
But she never even woke up to see it.

124
00:23:44,790 --> 00:23:46,940
So what did I do all this for?

125
00:23:52,070 --> 00:23:54,340
I’m all alone now.

126
00:23:55,600 --> 00:23:59,990
I have no one left in this world.
No one at all.

127
00:24:07,910 --> 00:24:09,330
That’s not true.

128
00:24:22,770 --> 00:24:24,430
I’m right here, aren’t I?

129
00:24:31,350 --> 00:24:32,530
Not just me.

130
00:24:33,280 --> 00:24:37,590
There are hundreds of people in
this hall, and millions more in the world.

131
00:24:38,090 --> 00:24:39,870
You’re not alone in this world.

132
00:25:05,990 --> 00:25:07,600
I’m not good at comforting people.

133
00:25:09,560 --> 00:25:14,050
But if you think like that,
wouldn’t your grandmother be sad?

134
00:25:25,520 --> 00:25:27,120
Have you tried that noodle place yet?

135
00:25:27,150 --> 00:25:28,270
- No.
- Not yet.

136
00:25:28,390 --> 00:25:30,800
You have to try it — it’s really good.

137
00:25:31,110 --> 00:25:33,490
- There were so many people lining up.
- Yeah.

138
00:25:33,520 --> 00:25:37,160
But you won’t get a chance after graduation.
The owner said she’s going back to farming.

139
00:25:38,230 --> 00:25:39,000
What a pity.

140
00:25:39,030 --> 00:25:41,240
What should I do?
Will she remember me?

141
00:25:43,520 --> 00:25:45,560
But I want to thank her.

142
00:25:46,840 --> 00:25:48,000
What to do, Rann?

143
00:25:59,650 --> 00:26:00,680
Where did she go?

144
00:26:04,130 --> 00:26:05,030
Looking for me?

145
00:26:16,270 --> 00:26:18,090
Well? Who are you looking for?

146
00:26:19,080 --> 00:26:23,000
Umm... well… uh…

147
00:26:23,130 --> 00:26:24,330
What is it, Nong Noo?

148
00:26:25,200 --> 00:26:26,400
Go ahead and say it.

149
00:26:26,970 --> 00:26:28,970
- ‘Noo’ is not my name.
- Oh?

150
00:26:29,730 --> 00:26:33,660
You keep referring to yourself as ‘Noo,’
so I thought that was your name.

151
00:26:33,690 --> 00:26:34,700
That’s not it at all.

152
00:26:37,700 --> 00:26:38,730
Well…

153
00:26:40,050 --> 00:26:42,210
I wanted to thank you for…

154
00:26:43,880 --> 00:26:44,890
the other day.

155
00:26:46,020 --> 00:26:47,780
You've taken care of your grandma's affairs?

156
00:26:48,650 --> 00:26:50,290
It’s all done. Noo—

157
00:26:54,120 --> 00:26:56,320
My name is Rann, Cohort 17.

158
00:26:59,300 --> 00:27:02,260
So… what’s your name?

159
00:27:03,870 --> 00:27:06,980
Lené, Ledarin Asawachun. Cohort 15.

160
00:27:08,800 --> 00:27:09,740
Sorry?

161
00:27:09,840 --> 00:27:11,300
You asked for my name,

162
00:27:11,320 --> 00:27:14,530
but you didn’t say whether you meant
my real name, nickname, or surname.

163
00:27:29,830 --> 00:27:31,870
Or you can call me P’ Le.

164
00:27:35,390 --> 00:27:36,360
Noo Rann.

165
00:27:53,130 --> 00:27:55,260
See you later.

166
00:27:55,860 --> 00:27:57,310
- Huh?
- ‘Huh’ what?

167
00:27:57,710 --> 00:27:59,020
I’d better get back to drawing.

168
00:27:59,960 --> 00:28:01,610
P’ Le, sawasdee ka.
I’ll head off now.

169
00:28:10,480 --> 00:28:11,780
Do you need something, P’ Le?

170
00:28:12,180 --> 00:28:15,260
Aren’t you going to ask who I’m waiting for?

171
00:28:15,550 --> 00:28:16,670
Who are you waiting for?

172
00:28:21,020 --> 00:28:22,030
You’re waiting for me?

173
00:28:23,620 --> 00:28:24,490
Me?

174
00:28:24,790 --> 00:28:26,450
Why are you so shocked?

175
00:28:28,630 --> 00:28:31,650
So what were you waiting for me for?

176
00:28:36,640 --> 00:28:37,310
Let’s go.

177
00:28:39,300 --> 00:28:40,110
Where to?

178
00:28:42,000 --> 00:28:43,010
To eat.

179
00:28:44,440 --> 00:28:46,570
Before someone gets all whiny from being hungry.

180
00:28:48,270 --> 00:28:51,470
Me? I’ve already eaten.

181
00:28:51,940 --> 00:28:54,780
You’re the one looking for
a lunch buddy, aren’t you?

182
00:28:55,560 --> 00:28:58,270
Come on, walk a bit and you’ll get hungry again.

183
00:28:59,190 --> 00:29:00,660
Let's go, you crybaby.

184
00:29:01,220 --> 00:29:05,300
Who’s the crybaby?
I only cried in front of you once.

185
00:29:06,510 --> 00:29:09,800
You’re getting good at
talking back to your senior now.

186
00:29:33,270 --> 00:29:34,420
Do you know, P’Le?

187
00:29:35,080 --> 00:29:39,300
Ever since that day, my world
has never been the same again.

188
00:30:03,880 --> 00:30:05,580
Can we take a look at the photos?

189
00:30:08,460 --> 00:30:10,390
- Aww, so cute!
- Aww, so cute!

190
00:30:12,990 --> 00:30:14,920
P’ Le, congratulations.

191
00:30:15,170 --> 00:30:16,980
Don’t forget to come back and visit us.

192
00:30:18,230 --> 00:30:21,880
Not sure if you’ll visit us.
But I’m sure that…

193
00:30:22,210 --> 00:30:23,210
You talk too much.

194
00:30:24,270 --> 00:30:26,360
I only talk this much with you.

195
00:30:27,760 --> 00:30:29,500
P’ Le, please take care of my friend.

196
00:30:30,620 --> 00:30:31,630
I’ll look after her.

197
00:30:35,860 --> 00:30:39,620
Hey. Stop making that sulky face.

198
00:30:42,300 --> 00:30:45,370
What am I to you anyway?
Why would you look after me?

199
00:30:57,490 --> 00:30:59,640
You look like I’m already dead.

200
00:31:00,340 --> 00:31:01,550
Watch your mouth.

201
00:31:01,860 --> 00:31:05,240
Who jinxes themselves on a day like this?
Smack your own mouth now.

202
00:31:07,280 --> 00:31:08,300
So fierce.

203
00:31:13,500 --> 00:31:14,350
Boop.

204
00:31:15,530 --> 00:31:18,130
I’m just graduating.
We’ll see each other again.

205
00:31:23,360 --> 00:31:28,080
You say that now, but before you know
it, we’ll only be meeting at class reunions.

206
00:31:28,310 --> 00:31:30,160
Or once every ten years.

207
00:31:34,560 --> 00:31:35,340
Okay.

208
00:31:37,690 --> 00:31:40,110
If you ever want to see me, just give me a call.

209
00:31:40,930 --> 00:31:44,980
No matter where I am... I’ll fly straight to you.

210
00:31:53,290 --> 00:31:54,720
You promise?

211
00:32:04,110 --> 00:32:05,150
I promise.

212
00:32:20,330 --> 00:32:21,890
Surprise!

213
00:32:24,160 --> 00:32:26,970
Congratulations to Khun Ledarin Asawachun

214
00:32:27,010 --> 00:32:29,330
on taking up your new
position at the company.

215
00:32:30,710 --> 00:32:35,000
Now you’re beautiful, talented, and wealthy too.

216
00:32:35,800 --> 00:32:38,380
Are you going to forget this junior of yours?

217
00:32:40,190 --> 00:32:41,680
So you remember my name now?

218
00:32:43,500 --> 00:32:45,150
I remembered it from the very first time.

219
00:32:47,610 --> 00:32:50,130
So aren’t you going to take the flowers?

220
00:32:50,990 --> 00:32:53,730
Of course, I will.
They’re from you after all.

221
00:33:01,690 --> 00:33:03,170
Is something wrong, P’ Le?

222
00:33:04,770 --> 00:33:06,130
You looked kind of spaced out.

223
00:33:10,280 --> 00:33:11,200
It’s nothing.

224
00:33:15,520 --> 00:33:18,870
Just work—I’m a little stressed about it.

225
00:33:19,410 --> 00:33:22,240
Whoa, from the very first days?

226
00:33:23,330 --> 00:33:25,490
Working life is tough.

227
00:33:29,410 --> 00:33:31,330
Probably because I’m facing the real thing now.

228
00:33:36,780 --> 00:33:38,190
So what’s with these flowers?

229
00:33:40,790 --> 00:33:42,080
They’re flowers, of course.

230
00:33:43,670 --> 00:33:44,570
Gerberas.

231
00:33:46,380 --> 00:33:47,110
Pretty, right?

232
00:33:48,540 --> 00:33:49,540
That’s it?

233
00:33:49,620 --> 00:33:51,120
Does there have to be something more?

234
00:33:57,720 --> 00:33:59,880
I thought you were going to say,

235
00:34:00,300 --> 00:34:04,940
‘Flowers—they’re pretty. Just like you.’

236
00:34:05,540 --> 00:34:10,400
Or ‘Red gerberas are for someone special.’

237
00:34:10,980 --> 00:34:12,219
Something like that.

238
00:34:13,719 --> 00:34:14,949
So unromantic.

239
00:34:15,679 --> 00:34:20,010
At this rate… when will you get a lover?

240
00:34:22,800 --> 00:34:25,290
I’m starting to worry about you.

241
00:34:28,620 --> 00:34:30,130
Why do I have to be romantic anyway?

242
00:34:31,179 --> 00:34:33,040
I only brought you some flowers.

243
00:34:33,739 --> 00:34:38,679
And why are you worrying about
whether I’ll get a lover or not?

244
00:34:43,100 --> 00:34:44,210
I’m just worried…

245
00:34:46,320 --> 00:34:47,810
as your senior.

246
00:34:52,020 --> 00:34:53,800
If you don’t want them, then give them back.

247
00:34:57,130 --> 00:35:01,330
Next time, I’ll get you some flowers too.
Much bigger than these.

248
00:35:01,470 --> 00:35:03,290
You really have to compete with me over this?

249
00:35:04,760 --> 00:35:06,180
I just wanted to.

250
00:35:06,730 --> 00:35:09,660
Maybe you’ve forgotten,
but I happen to be rich.

251
00:35:10,830 --> 00:35:11,870
Very rich.

252
00:35:12,690 --> 00:35:13,800
What a show-off.

253
00:35:21,820 --> 00:35:22,850
So, do you like it?

254
00:35:26,970 --> 00:35:28,220
Surprise!

255
00:35:29,980 --> 00:35:31,230
What is this, P’ Le?

256
00:35:31,670 --> 00:35:32,840
Happy birthday.

257
00:35:40,890 --> 00:35:42,290
I want you to be happy.

258
00:35:43,390 --> 00:35:44,880
Happier than everyone else.

259
00:35:46,190 --> 00:35:49,980
The happiest in the whole world, Noo Rann.

260
00:36:07,460 --> 00:36:09,740
- P' Le...
- Get out of my sight.

261
00:36:28,200 --> 00:36:30,050
Aran, this is your professor.

262
00:36:30,350 --> 00:36:32,890
I’m calling to ask what you’ve
decided about the scholarship.

263
00:36:33,200 --> 00:36:34,720
You need to make a decision now.

264
00:36:42,100 --> 00:36:43,780
I’ll accept the scholarship, Professor.

265
00:36:43,850 --> 00:36:46,200
Alright, you should prepare the documents—

266
00:36:47,670 --> 00:36:49,030
Are you okay?

267
00:36:55,110 --> 00:36:56,390
I’m fine.

268
00:36:58,010 --> 00:36:59,630
I’ll go on to continue my studies.

269
00:37:06,190 --> 00:37:08,370
P’ Le

270
00:37:14,440 --> 00:37:17,610
The number you have dialed is currently unavailable.

271
00:37:18,520 --> 00:37:20,560
Didn’t you say you’d come if I called?

272
00:37:21,110 --> 00:37:25,200
Didn’t you say you’d come
whenever I wanted to see you?

273
00:37:29,430 --> 00:37:30,500
I’m sorry.

274
00:37:31,370 --> 00:37:34,010
It’s all my fault. I’m sorry.

275
00:37:34,800 --> 00:37:36,120
I’m sorry.

276
00:38:03,890 --> 00:38:08,190
Goodbye... my P’ Le.

277
00:38:38,950 --> 00:38:39,830
P’ Le!

278
00:39:01,610 --> 00:39:02,500
Finally cremated.

279
00:39:02,950 --> 00:39:06,850
I haven’t slept for four nights,
worried someone might inspect the body.

280
00:39:07,750 --> 00:39:09,130
Could’ve been done sooner.

281
00:39:09,380 --> 00:39:12,440
What about other pieces of evidence?
They specifically ordered that—

282
00:39:12,470 --> 00:39:17,040
Get rid of all the evidence related to the death,
the crime scene, the weapon, and the car.

283
00:39:17,540 --> 00:39:21,250
Who the hell do you think I am?
Couldn’t get any cleaner than this.

284
00:39:21,420 --> 00:39:24,930
Not to mention the top-tier acting
I had to pull off—crying at the funeral.

285
00:39:26,170 --> 00:39:30,290
There’s been a leak lately,
so the boss is worried about who’s behind it.

286
00:39:30,670 --> 00:39:31,890
If it’s not you, then fine.

287
00:39:40,030 --> 00:39:41,000
You heard it, right?

288
00:39:55,600 --> 00:39:56,910
Am I going to die?

289
00:40:02,170 --> 00:40:03,160
Grandma...

290
00:40:04,490 --> 00:40:06,290
I’m coming to you now.

291
00:40:08,310 --> 00:40:14,950
Dad… Mom… I’m sorry.
I didn’t live the life you hoped for.

292
00:40:16,590 --> 00:40:18,930
P’ Le, I’m sorry.

293
00:40:20,250 --> 00:40:24,360
If I had just one more chance,
I’d never run away like that.

294
00:40:25,410 --> 00:40:26,880
I’d stay by your side.

295
00:40:28,930 --> 00:40:31,900
I’d do anything to keep you alive.

296
00:40:33,490 --> 00:40:35,330
I want to see you again.

297
00:40:37,370 --> 00:40:38,450
Just once.

298
00:40:41,460 --> 00:40:42,320
Please…

299
00:40:44,970 --> 00:40:45,900
Just once.

300
00:40:50,070 --> 00:40:51,300
One more time.

301
00:41:15,800 --> 00:41:17,740
What... is this?

302
00:41:27,370 --> 00:41:28,300
My old room?

303
00:41:29,710 --> 00:41:32,120
No, no. I need to file a report.

304
00:41:32,590 --> 00:41:33,500
I need to call the police.

305
00:41:36,070 --> 00:41:37,850
Aran, this is your professor.

306
00:41:38,200 --> 00:41:41,390
- I’m calling to ask about the scholarship.
- I'll accept it.

307
00:41:41,410 --> 00:41:42,760
You need to make a decision now.

308
00:41:47,580 --> 00:41:49,400
Aran, this is your professor.

309
00:41:49,750 --> 00:41:52,330
I’m calling to ask what you’ve
decided about the scholarship.

310
00:41:52,610 --> 00:41:53,780
You need to make a decision—

311
00:41:57,460 --> 00:41:58,180
No way.

312
00:41:59,550 --> 00:42:00,520
This can't be real.

313
00:42:01,970 --> 00:42:02,790
No.

314
00:42:21,050 --> 00:42:22,160
2021.

315
00:42:25,280 --> 00:42:26,420
Five years ago.

316
00:42:29,120 --> 00:42:30,010
P' Le.

317
00:42:53,430 --> 00:42:54,880
P’ Le is still alive.

318
00:42:57,380 --> 00:42:58,450
She isn’t dead yet.

319
00:43:08,390 --> 00:43:13,620
~ As if the heavens saw my sorrow ~

320
00:43:13,940 --> 00:43:18,190
~ They guided us back to each other ~

321
00:43:18,660 --> 00:43:22,050
~ After the day we were suddenly torn apart ~

322
00:43:22,080 --> 00:43:26,680
~ They let me return to your side ~

323
00:43:27,100 --> 00:43:30,280
~ To know how much you mean to me ~

324
00:43:30,390 --> 00:43:33,860
~ And just how much I love you ~

325
00:44:06,450 --> 00:44:07,370
You heard it, right?

326
00:44:18,440 --> 00:44:19,600
This is real, Rann.

327
00:44:22,370 --> 00:44:23,590
You already died once.

328
00:44:27,670 --> 00:44:29,140
And this is your second chance.

329
00:44:32,110 --> 00:44:33,610
P’ Le is still alive.

330
00:44:43,150 --> 00:44:44,730
I don’t know what happened.

331
00:44:46,270 --> 00:44:47,890
But it won’t end the same way this time.

332
00:44:49,390 --> 00:44:50,530
I won’t let P’ Le die.

333
00:44:51,910 --> 00:44:52,940
I have to make it happen.

334
00:45:11,610 --> 00:45:13,880
Professor, it’s me.

335
00:45:14,850 --> 00:45:18,370
Sorry about earlier.
There was an urgent matter at home.

336
00:45:19,380 --> 00:45:22,060
As for the scholarship, I’ll accept it.

337
00:45:23,770 --> 00:45:24,780
I’ll go.

338
00:45:39,030 --> 00:45:41,090
There’s nothing I can do to help you now.

339
00:45:42,220 --> 00:45:45,660
Five years from now, you’ll be killed.

340
00:45:46,920 --> 00:45:49,880
I promise I’ll be back in time.

341
00:45:53,640 --> 00:45:54,740
I need to be more prepared.

342
00:45:56,760 --> 00:45:58,470
And I’ll find a way to stop it.

343
00:46:40,140 --> 00:46:41,530
I’m going to save you.

344
00:46:42,350 --> 00:46:46,180
Even if you still hate me by then, that’s okay.

345
00:46:47,240 --> 00:46:48,140
I promise.

346
00:47:27,280 --> 00:47:30,670
From now on, you’ll stay
with Grandma, sweetheart.

347
00:47:31,220 --> 00:47:33,180
I’ll take care of you.

348
00:47:49,650 --> 00:47:53,560
Do your best today, my little one.

349
00:47:53,960 --> 00:47:57,420
I’m not little anymore.
I’m in middle school now.

350
00:47:57,700 --> 00:48:03,090
Sure. You’re still wearing pigtails
and you say you’re not a kid?

351
00:48:03,910 --> 00:48:05,960
Not talking to you anymore.
I’d better go to school.

352
00:48:06,220 --> 00:48:07,110
Then go on.

353
00:48:17,100 --> 00:48:18,660
Grandma, gimme a hug.

354
00:48:19,040 --> 00:48:21,830
Is that how grown-ups talk now?

355
00:48:22,300 --> 00:48:23,840
Come on, Grandma.

356
00:48:37,040 --> 00:48:42,140
My little one has grown into a young lady already.

357
00:48:43,400 --> 00:48:48,190
No, I don’t want to be a young lady.
I’ll be your little one forever.

358
00:48:51,430 --> 00:48:55,050
Oh, aren’t you going to school anymore?

359
00:48:55,310 --> 00:48:57,740
Crap, I’m late! I’m going now.

360
00:48:59,720 --> 00:49:01,440
How dare you say “crap” to Grandma.

361
00:49:13,820 --> 00:49:15,940
Grandma, I got in.

362
00:49:16,940 --> 00:49:19,390
Grandma, I did it.

363
00:49:21,390 --> 00:49:22,270
Grandma?

364
00:49:23,490 --> 00:49:26,290
Grandma, I got admitted to university.

365
00:49:36,580 --> 00:49:38,900
Hello, may I speak with a family
member of Khun Manee, please?

366
00:49:39,660 --> 00:49:41,100
Yes, speaking.

367
00:49:41,400 --> 00:49:44,840
Your relative has been admitted
to the hospital with heart failure.

368
00:49:45,620 --> 00:49:49,250
She needs emergency surgery.
Please come sign the consent form immediately.

369
00:49:52,310 --> 00:49:54,400
Grandma, I’m sorry.

370
00:49:55,490 --> 00:49:57,920
I’ll be home late tonight.
There’s an event at my faculty.

371
00:49:59,640 --> 00:50:01,410
No need to make dinner for me.

372
00:50:33,350 --> 00:50:36,350
English Subtitles by Saowalak K.

373
00:50:37,290 --> 00:50:39,190
You really need to get a secretary.

374
00:50:39,960 --> 00:50:43,460
Starting today, I’ll be taking
on the role of your secretary.

375
00:50:43,930 --> 00:50:44,990
I’m being serious.

376
00:50:45,340 --> 00:50:47,920
Why did you come back?
What exactly do you want?

377
00:50:48,370 --> 00:50:52,100
What I know now is that P’ Le
may have been killed by someone.

378
00:50:52,500 --> 00:50:54,030
And the person involved is…

379
00:50:54,310 --> 00:50:56,880
The mastermind behind it all.
Who is he?

380
00:50:57,210 --> 00:50:59,310
Starting to get interested in me now?

381
00:50:59,720 --> 00:51:00,890
And your point is?
